caption: Tasty food with a comfortable and relaxed atmosphere.  LOVE that you can get gluten free injera here, although I suggest calling ahead to make sure it will be available.  Currently, they require logging your name in a book, masks while not eating, and temp checks.  Outdoor seating and indoor seating with clear plastic dividers available. Friendly staff and good service speed.  Would definitely go back again.

I have recently discovered Benyam and I think it's the best Ethiopian Restaurant in NYC. The food is really fresh and tasty but not heavy and the place itself is super clean. I go there with my husband and my 3 year old and we all enjoy it a lot!
Very yummy!
The food was great! The staff is very friendly! We will definitely be back.
Good Hospitality, Excellent Food, and Amazing Customer Service. Drove from Long Island can see myself Returning
I ordered spicy Asa Tibs tonight - holy moly, wow, best meal I’ve had since Covid/quarantine entered the picture. Looking forward to ordering again!
Everything was truly delicious! But it would have been nice to have injira in a separate takeout container from the dishes.
Got food for take out this stormy evening. Everyone is wearing masks. Even the cook in the kitchen wearing a face shield! Good food!

This is, hands down, the BEST Ethiopian food I've ever tasted. Actually, this might be the most delicious food I've ever had in general. It's family run, which makes it feel homey and the food is just SO delicious

I discovered Benyam during the pandemic.  At that time, only take out service was available. The owners far exceeded safeguards to protect their customers and themselves. The food is better than any other Ethiopian food I have had anywhere in the United States.  I travel about 50 blocks to pick up my meals, and it is never a burden because I know when I arrive home I will have the best meal of the week.

I like this spot! They give splendid meals, their menu is nice, The cook in that place is a real pro, I love a lot tasting all their food. The dishes are consistently of high class, the attitude towards the guests  is helpful. I often go to  this place and I not even once was discontended.  I highly recommend it.
The food is authentic, tasty and it seems to be made with healthier ingredients than your average Ethiopian food—they use lighter oils and butter. This is my new favorite Ethiopian restaurant.
Amazing and delicious food!
Cute little spot with delicious food. The workers are nice and helpful if in doubt with the menu. Price is reasonable.

Happened upon this little gem while waiting for a show at the Fillmore.I was so pleasantly surprised by how delicious their signature cocktail was and how incredibly welcoming and accommodating the staff were.What a gem.Loved the live piano and horn playing.I will be back to the city and make a trip specifically just to eat and drink and be entertained.
Decadent cocktails and authentic cuisine. Chic atmosphere with warm welcoming, however, the musicians on the night that I went need more cough passion. The owners and staff are super sweet tho.
If you are in New York looking for Ethiopian restaurant,  this is the right place to eat.

Really glad we found this restaurant! The food is amazing--it's clear that they use freshly-ground spices rather than mixes that have been sitting on the shelf. The sidewalk seating is lovely with all of the plants. This just might be our new Ethiopian spot!
Best Ethiopian food I’ve had in the city!

The food was incredible, make sure you get the Awaze Tibs. The waiter is very warm and hospitable, and they have outdoor dining during this time as well which is very helpful. Been to Ethiopian restaurants that were dingy but this one was clean, modern, and upbeat. Would definitely recommend!
Food is amazing. Had the meat and veggie platter and it was quite tasteful, all the right amount of spices and herbs. Hope to go back when we can actually dine in
Incredible restaurant. The food is delicious and the staff is friendly and welcoming. They also display new art pieces regularly which is fascinating.
Delicious food in a warm and joyful atmosphere.
My first time having Ethiopian cuisine and it was delicious. The service was excellent and they were very friendly, and hospitable. Definitely will be going back.
Great food. Great atmosphere with art done by one of the cooks!
Wonderful food! Great service!
Casual place, unpretentious, unassuming. Food was very alright and prices were pretty good. Service was attentive and caring.
The food here is always amazing and auntie is always polite and attentive. I so glad that I live right down the block.
Delicious and fairly priced. I highly recommend.
Very nice little Ethiopian restaurant. I recommend it without hesitation.
The ethiopian food is authentic and great. The lady who seems to be the owner is very friendly and makes you feel valued. I've dined at Benyam multiple times and will be going again.
This place is close to home and the owners and staff are so pleasant. The food is ALWAYS good. Try the Lentil Sambusa and whatever you get always the Shiro Wat as part of your dish!

Great experience,  great food, great host. Benyam himself coached us through the menu as several of us were first-time Ethiopian diners. I got the sampler for one and loved everything on it. Awesome flavors. Quick service for a lunch break of four people. Looking forward to bringing back a date here later. Though make sure you  are comfortable eating with your fingers in front of whoever you bring.
This is my favorite Ethiopian spot in the city. Tasty flavors, positive energy, and warm staff.

Relatively good place. Nice decor, friendly staff. I’m not an expert on Ethiopian food, but I wasn’t dissatisfied. Had the combo for 2 and most dishes were tasty. The only disappointments were the honey wine and the absence of Ethiopian style coffee. And only dessert was baklava. Would give 3.5 stars if possible.
Food was absolutely delicious, highly recommend. The staff was also very helpful in helping us pick our food!
We got the meat/vegetable sampler, and every dish was a winner. Will definitely be coming back.
Delicious food!
Standard Ethiopian food.  Great host and service.
Very delicious but the portions are smaller compared to other Ethiopian restaurants.
The food was amazing,  and really sweet waiters!!
Cozy Indian restaurant
Delicious food.
Nice place in Harlem. Ethiopian cousine and live music on last fridays night 😀😀😀
Amazing service & amazing food! I have been wanting to try Ethiopian food for so long.
Amazing, authentic food with friendly service
(Translated by Google) Cute ooo  (Original) Lindo ooo

Fantastic food, cool modern vibe. You can tell that it's a family run place. I brought my brother here for him to try Ethiopian food for the first time and it was a great decision. We got the azifa appetizer and veggie combo. Everything was great and tasty. We called ahead to get freshly made gluten free injera. Everything was worth it.
Had a very good experience in this spot with my daughter. The food was served quick and the customer service is just excellent. Prices are affordable.
Good portions, delicious food, and nice family/staff. Price could be a bit more affordable. Definitely my favorite in NYC!
Amazing food and service
Had Ethiopian food for the first time here and I liked it! The place is cute and comfy, the customer service was very nice, and food was tasty. I'll be back!
Great experience. Food, culture and atmosphere. Order the sample platter- vegan is very good.

Incredible food in a very cool space; modern decor combined with old and new Ethiopian art. I'd highly recommend the combo sampler for 2; it can easily feed 3 or 4. The Ethiopian beers aren't very distinctive, being either light or malty lagers, but the honey wine is. Service is excellent; don't be afraid to ask for recommendations (or even Amharic pronunciation tips!).
Really tasty , quick and friendly service
Decent for meat eaters.. Vegans run away...
Authentic and delicious Ethiopean food in a nice family atmosphere also great choice for Vegan
We order the veg and the non-veg platters. Don't recall the names. But the meat was tender and flavorful. Must try if in the neighborhood!
Delicious finger licking food. We cleaned the plate literally. Food choices and honey wine selection is top class. The hostess was very kind and friendly.
Good food love the Services they provide
A bit overpriced but certainly one of the better Ethiopian restaurants in the city.
Loved the food and ambience. Very traditional design. Friendly staff. Would live to visit again.
It was delicious and the staff offered me fresh cold water which was good. The injera was fresh and the portions was just enough for me. I will go back.

Overpriced slop. I traveled from Westchester county for a first time trying Ethiopian food. Nasty and flavorless. Small portions. I went somewhere else (wont shame this place with their competition) and they blew this place out the water and the portions were bigger, had more flavor and each dish was cheaper by at least 4 dollars. This place is close to a police precinct and you can barely find parking. I had to double park and wait 30 min for food that sucked...I do not recommend for their prices.Just my opinion but beware especially if youve never had the food before. They serve their takeout in styrofoam containers with the food slapped on the bread they give you then they cover it up making it soggy and the sauces to the food soak in...Never again. Not worth the money gas or my taste buds. In all fairness though the people who work there are friendly but friendliness has nothing to do with presentation and taste.
Delicious food at great prices. It's Ethiopian so you'll need to eat with your hands! (Which is part of the fun.)

I was totally bummed out when the restaurant that was at this location before Benyam, La Nomade, closed. They had great lamb and chicken dishes, and on Saturday or Sunday you could get some wicked fish ball soup! If you ordered early enough. Then Benyam popped up. It took me a while to come in for the first time but eventually the art on the inside and the little stand of potted plants on the outside drew me in. I immediately regretted waiting so long. The food is phenomenal! It seems a little pricey but the ingredients are quality and the portions are good so you do get what you pay for. The fellas who work there, and the matriarch of the place, are always genuinely friendly and act like it’s their pleasure to serve you. No really! It’s kinda crazy how much love they put into the place and the food. My only complaint would be that when I call for take out (since I live across the street I always get take out) it takes a bit long. But then I go in and see Benyam serving all these happy people who have seemingly trekked uptown or in from out of town for some delicious food and I don’t mind the wait as much. It’s manna from heaven!
Always authentic, full of true flavors, very soft and tasty injera. Best Ethiopian food in NYC

It's only the second time I've eaten Ethiopian food, but I found it so tasty and full of flavour. My partner is vegan and he loved their vegetarian options. Some other guest at our table chose a meat dish and that was equally delicious. The staff was really nice and made me feel welcome. No doubt we will come back.

I have eaten at nearly every Ethiopian restaurant in Toronto and New York, and Benyam is the best I've found in NYC and on par with my favorite in Toronto (Nazareth). The food is richly flavored, the njera fresh and generous, and the service efficient and friendly. One time they even offered me extra sauce to finish my njera. Very highly recommended.

Vegan-friendly* - their vegetable sides are not made with kibbeh (clarified butter), but do prepare meat in the same kitchen. My friend and I shared a vegetable sampler for 2 - great deal for an amazing amount of delicious food!

My favorite place in the neighborhood. The food is amazing, there is an abundance of spice and flavor in every dish. The owners are a joy to be around and between the food, their hospitality, and the way they have set up their space I always enjoy coming.

Perfection. Benyam has legit earned every single star. I do not believe there is one Ethiopian restaurant in the tri-state area that can claim 5-start status on yelp. The meat/veggie combo dish I ordered was well executed. The lamb besiga was tender, well-seasoned without being over salted. The lamb wot melted in my mouth as did the doro. The sides of shiro and gomen were expected but cooked so perfectly. Add'l vegetable sides are only $4!  You can tell each dish is cooked with pure love. And when asked how she managed to blow me away, the chef (owner's sister) echoed those sentiments. She literally said she loves to cook for people and see them enjoy her food. I wish she lived in my home and cooked for me every day. But alas I would never lose my "baby" weight.
Excellent Ethiopian food. A must try. Vegetarian options are fabulous too.

Went to dinner Tuesday 22nd Jan, BEST ETHIOPIAN MEAL EVER any where and service was unbelievable GREAT VALUE GREAT FOOD GREAT PEOPLE if you are in America or even UK and want an Ethiopian meal travel to here.  Thank you
Wonderful flavors and very friendly people.

We went here for the first time and it was clear before we even got our meal why nearly every table was taken - the aromas of the cooking food were heavenly and the food was even better. I can't believe it's taken us so long to come but we will definitely be back. Also, the portions were generous and we went home stuffed, with leftovers. If you're thinking to check this place out, don't hesitate any longer. I just wish we had gone sooner!
Great food, warm family atmosphere, coffee is great too! A little pricey but worth it. Share a dish ;)
amazing authentic Ethiopian spot, one of the best in nyc!
Amazing home-style Ethiopian food, with enough options to accommodate picky eaters. Definitely stop by if you are in the area.
I almost hate to rate this place, since then it'll get crowded.  Not fancy, but it's the best Ethiopian food I've had anywhere.

DELICIOUS. I went on a 'taste every Ethiopian restaurant north of 110th street' adventure I designed and found Benyam to be my favorite. The staff is wonderful, the vibe in the restaurant is homey and hip and the taste of each dish and njera is my favorite in the neighborhood. I am thankful they are so close and wish there was a monthly meal plan option. :)
super friendly
Love the vibe with great local art on the walls for sale. Place is small but good service. I like how they make scramble eggs. Baklava also tasty not too sweet. Also liked the beer.
Come here to eat until you have gastritis. So good. Especially the kitfo.  @curiosopher

Mildly seasoned, sensibly portioned dishes; not ideal for anyone who has never had Ethiopian food before as the staff does not volunteer much information about the food. Gomen (collard greens) unlike other Ethiopian variations I've had, these were more blanched than sauteed down which allowed them to keep much of their own natural flavor and crispness.
Wonderful ambiance, great customer service and most importantly delicious food.

Best Ethiopian restaurant in the city, I have been to many different restaurants over the years and as far as CUSTOMER SERVICE and FOOD /FLAVOR this is the BEST I've seen yet in the city! Many may have great flavors but avgerage or not good customer service. Some may have great customer service but lacking flavor and portions.Beyam is  CONSISTENT &  maintain GREAT FLAVOR AND CUSTOMER SERVICE I ACTUALLY FEEL LIKE FAMILY WHEN I GO THERE
Amazing Awaze dishes! Had a salad and beef with Awaze sauce - so good! Usually, berbere sauce dishes are my favorite at Ethiopian restaurants. Perhaps stick to Awaze dishes at Benyam?

My best friend and I had an amazing dinner here. The staff is super friendly and such great conversation. The chef's have an incredible talent and even their special BeNY is delicious. I've had my share of Ethiopian and this doesn't disappoint. The decor is also super cute. Oh and try the sweet wine!!!  I've never had anything like it. We got there at 6 and didn't leave until almost 1030 since we, the couple next to us, and the staff were having a great time chatting. I will definitely be back!
Delicious delicious food and great service. Will return.
Nice Place.

This is the place I take any out of towners for a great dining experience. Unbelievable flavors, and exquisite ever changing art adorning the walls. The staff is welcoming, warm, and professional. We recognized the owner at the neighborhood grocery store on an off day and felt like we were sighting a local celebrity! I cannot recommend this place strongly enough.
Nice place
Great food and super friendly staff.
One if the best Ethiopian options in the city
Very tasty food! Atmosphere was wonderful with beautiful afro-centric artwork made in house. Staff was super helpful and attentive. I will definitely be back to dine.
We always have a wonderful meal at Benyam. It is a welcoming place for sure. The cooking is high quality and delicious.
Wow

Really love Ethiopian food, and have tried it from all over the place including different states and countries but this one by far was the worst one I've tried. Really didnt get to taste the flavor in the doro wot as my order came only with dry chicken, not even the sauce its cooked in. I ended up having to drink the injera down since the chicken was dry and the sauce wasn't there. Never going back to this place as there are many other Ethiopian restaurants around the city, which I have been going too for years but wanted to try something new
Great hand eating food!! Finally a place where you don't need Forks and Spoons 😂
Meh.. good service very quaint place . Small portions but ok. Chic kool vibe..
refreshing Ethiopian food with excellent service
Great customer service. Great meal.

Cozy, casual, Ethiopian restaurant, serving delicious, authentic cuisine right around the corner from home in Harlem. The hosts are gracious, kind and friendly. Try the combination platter that includes a little bit of all their tasty delights.
Nice
Authentic Ethiopian food with eclectic art pieces and excellent service
Food was okay but portions were way too small, especially for the relatively higher prices compared with other NYC Ethiopian restaurants.
Delicious...must try

The food was so delicious. I fell in love with the artwork as well. I could taste almost every spice in the food. Everything was excellent and very filling. I took the rest to go and woke up craving my food ! The host was very kind and seemed so genuine..i will be returning on my next day off.
Great place
Fabulous
So glad this place opened up. The friendliest owners who happen to serve delicious food!
Benyam is run by a mother-son team: he's the front of the house and she's the cook. They're both quite friendly, the food is good, and the artwork on the walls is eclectic.
I haven't eaten there you yet, but I heard its good.
Great food for vegetarians for reasonable prices.
I got the Fitfit appetizer and the sampler entrée. Staff were kind and helpful, and the food was great!
Clean friendly environment

Charming space with art on walls, some pieces created by a member of the family that owns the business; all members were affable and polite; service was prompt; portion was spot on; delicious and aromatic vegetables/meats consumed with only fingers and ingera (a crepe-like bread); outstanding introduction to Habesha megeb (Ethiopian food)!

Truly awesome Ethiopian restaurant!  Besides tender and delicious food, the owner is charming and friendly.  We were the only customers when they opened for the day and he kept us rapt in conversation until our food was ready.
Very cool authentic place, nice atmosphere and good service
Wow just wow....great food and great service
Excellent authentic cuisine.
Delicious and great vibe!

We arrived with a party of six and a baby and we were seated and given drinks right away. Benyam is an amazing guy and we didn't even order. We just explained that we wanted to try a little of everything and he brought us out some delicious apps and then a full family style meal that included lamb and chicken. As I tried each dish I could tell with each bite that not only was the food made with quality ingredients but it was home cooked with love. It was one of those meals that I will surely never forget! Excellent food, Superb service, and a comfortable atmosphere for friends and family alike. Two thumbs up and many thanks. :-)
Great Ethiopian restaurant in central Harlem. Food is very good and service is also great and friendly. Place is cosy with beautiful paintings. I definitely recommend this restaurant!
The food was delicious! Very friendly family that runs the place. So glad this restaurant has opened in the neighborhood.
Great space, very friendly staff, very good food and portions!

First time last night -- very excited this is in the neighborhood. Long, leisurely dinner, appetizers, entrees and sides were delicious. Excellent service and pleasant atmosphere. Especially liked the lentil dishes and the Tibs Wot.

Great place to experience Ethiopian food, The place is open and cozy, the ambiance is light and artsy, the food is tasty and portions are good. The hosts are friendly and welcoming. Give them a try, you won't be disappointed!
Had a fantastic time at BeNYAM Ethiopian Cuisine! I have added it to my rotation of go-to spots within in the neighborhood.  P.S. The baklava is incredible!
